data.description: Come take a look at this 3-bed, 1.5-bath residence at 328 Cleveland St in Historic Bristol Borough. This  home features a spacious front porch, back porch, and a backyard, with the main floor comprising of a large living room, dining room, eat-in kitchen area, half bath, with easy access to the back yard and back alley. The second floor includes 3 bedrooms, a family area, a full bath, a back deck and plenty of closet space. The capacious basement can be utilized for storage or, if you are so inclined and feeling ambitious, a recreational space. New features include a new roof (replaced one 1 year ago), refurbished hardwood (refurbished 2 years ago), and a new air conditioning wall unit on 2nd fl (replaced 1 year ago). Located in the Harriman section of Bristol Borough, the neighborhood is a pleasant community within walking distance of the Bristol Borough train station, the Delaware Canal State Park, and the Bristol riverfront. Come turn this house into your home!
